Name: 71, Swanbourne
Main Risk: Poor or no provision for cyclists
Description: I ride along this road frequently to train at Bold Park, and I am constantly scared as the cars are way too close and the bike lane nowhere near big enough. The cars go past so fast even trucks. There is so much verge on the side of the road so why not make a bike path along side it?
Comment 1: Rod: I had the misfortune of having a flat tyre here and as the road narrows from 4 to 2 lanes of traffic, it always is a bottleneck. In addition the number of heavy vehicles on this road and no safe verge area to get off the roadway makes it a very dangerous road to replace a tyre. There is plenty of room to expand this road with another 2 lanes and this section of road is only about 500 metres in length, making it a small job for main roads to make it safe.
Comment 2: David: Traveling North on West Coast Highway before Alfred Road the road is duel carrigeway and after where highway No 65 joins it it is duel carrigeway. This section of highway (about 2klm.) is single lane in each direction.Its a bottleneck, vehicles overtake and push into the flow of traffic; All the land is there, very little earth works required, no intersections to upgrade, ... so the cost cant be too much to bring west coast highway up to a duel carigeway standard
Comment 7: trucks travelling well over the speed limit that can barely stay within the lane, motorists driving in the cycling lane
